From Scott Dorsey Subject Re History question In article snap mrc Paul Johnson writes I recall reading of a phonograph which used mechanical Compressed air was squirted out of a valve which was controlled by the The result was noisy and distinctly lo fi but much louder than a conventional It tended to wear the disks out pretty quickly This was the Pathe you are thinking of although there were other It didn't wear the disks any more than conventional acoustic designs but it did have a high noise level due to the continual hiss of escaping There are a lot of them still operating and they are pretty There was a pneumatic amplifier designed by Alexander Graham Bell as well but I don't know if it was ever scott